
This is a wordpress with keycloak env running on docker.

1. clone repo and cd into it
2. run ./run.sh from the command line - 2 containers will build and run and output the urls once complete.

3. Set up wordpress with any detail and note.
4. activate JWT Authentication for WP-API, JWT Authenticator, or OAuth Client as required.
5. log into keycloak1 & 2 (use incognito for 2nd keycloak) master realm http://localhost:8080/auth ;

username: admin
password: admin

6. Import demo-realm-export.json using the import tool within keycloak gui for keycloak1
7. Configure keycloak2 as federated server between keycloak1
